==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unwisdom
<hw>Un*wis"dom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Want of wisdom;
unwise conduct or action; folly; simplicity; ignorance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sumptuary laws are among the exploded fallacies which we have
outgrown, and we smile at the <qex>unwisdom</qex> which could except to
regulate private habits and manners by statute.</q> <rj><qau>J. A.
Froude.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unwise</ent>⟦br⟧
